 and became more massive than their counterparts in disc\ngalaxies. This suggests that in this halo mass range the ellipticals are less\nmassive because AGN feedback ejected more of the halo's gas reservoir, reducing\nstar formation, and suppressing the (re)growth of stellar discs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Oct 2020 20:23:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-14"}
